text: Korkeasaari () is an island in Helsinki, Finland. The exact meaning of Korkeasaari is "Tall Island/Islet". It is part of the Mustikkamaaâ€“Korkeasaari district. It has Finland's largest and oldest zoo, called Korkeasaari Zoo. The island of Korkeasaari is a rocky island. Two smaller islands are located next to it: Hylkysaari and Palosaari. ==Other websites== * Helsinki Zoo website Category:Islands of Europe Category:Geography of Finland Category:Helsinki
